title: MSU's Calhoun picks up third career Big Ten weekly honor
text:
MSU's Calhoun picks up third career Big Ten weekly honor FOX Sports 
Oct 19, 2015 at 2:02p ET + 
Shilique Calhoun had another huge game against Michigan. Mike Carter / USA Today Sports FOX Sports   2:02p ET 
Michigan State defensive end Shilique Calhoun did not turn in the unbelievable game-winning play for the Spartans on Saturday at Michigan, but he had a lot to do with MSU staying close enough to make that possible. 
After notching a career-high 3.5 tackles for loss against the Wolverines, Calhoun was named Big Ten Defensive Player of the Week for the third time in his career and the second time this season. 
Two of those stops in the backfield were sacks. 
He also won the award on the last weekend of September. MORE NEWS: Want stories delivered to you? Sign up for our College Football newsletters.
